# React & TypeScript Conventions

## Components

- Functional components only, exported as named functions: `export function MyComponent() {}`
- Props interface defined above the component, not exported:
  ```tsx
  interface MyComponentProps {
    title: string
    onClose: () => void
  }
  export function MyComponent({ title, onClose }: MyComponentProps) { ... }
  ```
- No `React.FC` — use explicit return types only when needed

## State & Callbacks

- Wrap all handlers passed as props in `useCallback` with correct deps
- Use `useRef` for mutable values that shouldn't trigger re-renders (z-index counters, drag state, timers)
- Pointer events (`onPointerDown/Move/Up`) for drag-and-drop (mouse + touch unified)
- Prevent double-click after drag: track `lastDragEnd` timestamp, ignore clicks within 300ms

## Types

- `WindowId` union and `WindowState` interface live in `src/types.ts`
- Use `import type { ... }` for type-only imports
- Adding a new window type requires updating: `WindowId` union, `WINDOW_DEFAULTS` in `useWindowManager.ts`, render logic in `App.tsx`

## SVG Icons

- Defined as React components in `Icons.tsx` accepting `{ size?: number }`
- Use inline SVG (no external icon libraries)
- Keep paths simple, ME-era aesthetic: 16×16 viewBox, solid fills, minimal gradients
